Evolution goes down TOMORROW @lulalounge 🤯❤️‍🔥

You really do not want to miss this show! There’s a couple tickets left via Eventbrite so make sure you get yours here: https://www.eventbrite.ca/e/evolution-presented-by-city-centre-dance-tickets-465270294977

We got live dancers, singers, dinner, and an afterparty! What more could you ask for? 😍

Come see how we do things over @citycentre_dance - I’m so proud of everyone involved! The students have really grown, and we have some of the best teachers periodttttt! 🙌🏽

EVOLUTION by City Centre Dance was everything and more 🥹

Firstly, thank you and congratulations to everyone involved with this show! From the performers, choreographers, staff, and volunteers! You all had a huge role to play, and it wouldn’t have been possible with each and every single one of you. 

To our Program Students, wow - just wow! You all went above and beyond any expectations and consistently raised the bar! Your teachers could not be more proud of you for working so hard and absolutely smashing all of your choreography! Thank you for your hard work, dedication, and consistency over the past 10-Weeks. We hope you all feel happy and proud of yourselves because you deserve it! We can’t wait to continue training you. 

To the faculty - thank you all for your unwavering support, loyalty, and commitment to CCD and your students. All of you came in for extra rehearsals, helped clean, and supported every aspect of the show. I feel so lucky to have you all a part of my team, and will be in your corner for as long as I am in this industry. Love you all so very much - you are my family 🤍

To the guest performers - thank you for sharing your gifts and talent with us and the community! You are all valued, and will forever have a platform with us! Congratulations on another exceptional performance ❤️‍🔥

To the volunteers and helpers - literally, we could not have done this without you so thank you for your help during the show because it ran so smoothly thanks to all of you! Your support does not go unnoticed and we love you! 

Lastly, thank you to @lulalounge for hosting us and being so awesome! And to all of the attendees, thank you for coming to the show!!! 

Until next time 😍

TIMELESS @donondanforth ♾️ 

Cheers & Congratulations to everyone on another successful show! Somehow we keep raising the bar and they keep on getting better and better! 

We’d like to give a huge shoutout to all of our 10-Week Showcase Program Students for outstanding performances on Wednesday night! You all worked extremely hard, went out of your comfort zones, and pushed yourselves to be able to pull off such tight routines! Thank you for your dedication to this program but more importantly to your own training. This community is one of the most beautiful, inclusive, and safe spaces within the GTA - and what makes it up is each and every single one of you. Our doors, ears, and hearts are always open for as long as you need us ❣️

A huge thank you to the faculty for your unwavering dedication, commitment, support, and hard work as always! You all never seem to fail at providing one of the best educational experiences that I’ve ever seen. It’s an honour to have you all a part of this company, as always thank you all for being you!

To all the staff, volunteers, guest performers! Our shows would be incomplete without all of you! So thank you for being a part of it and giving it your all every single time! We are so proud and honoured to have you. 

Until next time,
Alex 💞

Hey Friends! I’m excited to share that I’ve partnered with @primevideoca this Pride for their #NotJustForShow Campaign! Our goal is to create awareness and advocate for further 2SLGBTQ+ representation in Film and Television so that our stories can be told. I’m so honoured to share my feelings about the current climate of representation within Film and Television as someone who works as a Professional Dancer and Actor in the entertainment industry. To view the full video and to hear from creators within our community, head to https://www.notjustforshow.ca to watch and learn more! #ad
